table_caption: Demographics and clinical characteristics of the study population.
table_foot: Note: Data are presented as median (Q1, Q3). N represents the number of patients. p values reported in bold denote statistical significance at p < .05 (Kruskal‐Wallis test, FDR corrected).Abbreviations: Aβ42, amyloid β 42; AD, Alzheimer's disease patients; CU, cognitively unimpaired subjects; GMVF, gray matter volume fraction; MCI, mild cognitive impairment patients; MMSE, Mini‐Mental State Examination; nAD, non Alzheimer's disease degenerative patients; P‐tau, phosphorylated tau; T‐tau, total tau; WMLVF, white matter lesion volume fraction.
